n IDs (e.g. returning a stale pointer instead of null would walk the if-branch and chain into HandleRequestTarget with a non-zero data[4..7] = stale player's target → reply GameID=stale_target rather than literal 0); (e) proxy default-case ForwardClientOpcode dropping the opcode (0x0018 is not explicitly listed in proxy/ClientToServer_linux_stubs.cpp); (f) SendAuxShip side-effect regression — if a refactor flips HasDiff() to default-true the test would see an extra unexpected 0x001B AUX_DATA frame in the drain loop (not asserted as failure but provides a diagnostic signal); (g) ShipIndex()->SetTargetGameID(-1) null-deref. Per CLAUDE.md server-integrity: the wire shape and the literal SendSetTarget(0, -1) reply on unknown-player lookup are exactly what retail emits — the -1 sentinel propagation across both 0x0017 and 0x0018 paths is the canonical retail behaviour and we don't fabricate any side-channel."),
