OptionalVar would shift field offsets); (d) GetGameIDFromName crash on the empty-string lookup; (e) proxy default-case ForwardClientOpcode dropping the opcode (0x002D is not explicitly listed in proxy/ClientToServer_linux_stubs.cpp); (f) dispatcher mis-route at PlayerConnection.cpp:471 (case label immediately below 0x002C ACTION — a copy-paste swap would route 0x002D into HandleAction directly, mis-interpreting the 14B ActionPacket2 as a 16B ActionPacket); (g) HandleAction's pre-switch GetObjectFromID(-1) null-deref. Per CLAUDE.md server-integrity: the wire shape is exactly what retail Win32 client emits for a name-targeted action (cross-sector group-kick etc.), sub-action 23 (\"keep trading\") is a published retail value, empty-name no-such-player path is exactly how retail handles a stale/disconnected target name."),
